<!--template match = paragraph[descendant::heading]--><!--template match = heading--><title>Diagnosis</title>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
This species differs from species of the 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>H. angustulus</tp:taxon-name>
group of the 
Canary Islands
(
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref18966">Hoch &amp; Remane 1985</xref>
) in the following characters (1) it has, far basally, on the left lateroventral side of the theca, a short spine, directed caudally, of variable size and thickness, absent in the Canarian species (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">Fig. 12I–M</xref>
); (2) on the left ventral side, the long thorns are almost parallel and tips are not divergent.
</p>
