<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
BODY MEASUREMENTS (mm). VW: males: 0.20–0.28, 0.24 ± 0.02 (n = 21); females: 0.28–0.34, 0.30 ± 0.02 (n = 13). See also 
<!--template match = tableCitation--><xref>Table 1.</xref>
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
COLOURATION. As in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>H. madeires</tp:taxon-name>
(
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-7--189-232-1777-1803-">Fig. 3F</xref>
).
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
HEAD. Vertex, frons, clypeus and medial ocellus as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>H. madeires</tp:taxon-name>
, but the vertex is usually more elongated and the margins are usually parallel (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">Fig. 12A–B</xref>
).
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
THORAX. Pronotum, mesonotum, tegula, tegmina, and legs as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>H. madeires</tp:taxon-name>
(
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-7--189-232-1777-1803-">Figs 3F</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-12--189-232-1776-1802-">5E</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">12B</xref>
). MALE GENITALIA (see also 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref19883">Remane &amp; Hoch 1986</xref>
). Pygofer, anal tube, anal styles and parameres as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>H. madeires</tp:taxon-name>
(
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">Fig. 12C–H</xref>
). Body length, position, and curvature of the ventral spine, and the dorsocaudal thorns of the aedeagus as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>H. madeires</tp:taxon-name>
, but the thorns are almost parallel or divergent distally and sometimes the dorsal thorn medially touches the ventral spine (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">Fig. 12I–J</xref>
). The thorns extend along 4/5 of the aedeagus but without overlapping distally. The dorsal thorn is oblique and straight, and is basally directed towards the ventral spine (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">Fig. 12I–J</xref>
). The ventral thorn is thicker and longer than the dorsal; it is approximately 3 times as wide and thick in the middle part than it is at the base, and sometimes the ventral margin is slightly arched in the middle part; in dorsal and ventral view they cross (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-27--189-232-1778-1804-">Fig. 12K–M</xref>
).
</p>
