<!--template match = paragraph[descendant::heading]--><!--template match = heading--><title>Distribution and ecology</title>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Endemic to the island of 
Madeira
. It is present from low to medium altitudes within the xerophytic shrub communities of the south of the island both in the coastal regions and in the gorges. Adults occur from April to August on 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Globularia salicina</tp:taxon-name>
